cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the impact of downlink/uplink decoupling on LTE networks and proposes a model to estimate the decoupling region. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper formulates an equation to calculate the total power saved by devices due to decoupling, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the impact of decoupling on power consumption per device, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the potential use of the extra area due to decoupling to enable D2D pairs, which can involve multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not a major focus of the paper, the use of D2D communications can have security implications, which can fall under the domain of cryptography and security.
